# Analysis of Grid-Based Path Planning Algorithms

This project compares grid-based path planning algorithms including A*, Jump Point Search (JPS), and Theta*.

## Goals
- Measure runtime scalability across grid sizes
- Compare node expansions under varying obstacle densities
- Evaluate path quality and computational overhead
- Benchmark performance on synthetic 2D grid maps

## Algorithms
- A*
- JPS
- Theta*

## Project Structure
- `src/algorithms/`: path planning implementations
- `src/utils/`: grid generation, heuristics, visualization
- `experiments/`: benchmarking scripts
- `results/`: saved outputs
- `tests/`: unit tests

## Setup
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt